commit 46f7a72029dd82bbbc3d402f835452fca4cfaebb
Author: Bartłomiej Dach <dach.bartlomiej@gmail.com>
Date:   Tue Mar 17 11:01:04 2026 +0100

    Fix sourcegen structs using inefficient default equality members

    Relevant inspection: https://www.jetbrains.com/help/resharper/DefaultStructEqualityIsUsed.Global.html

    The two fixes are to generate the equality members or to use `record
    struct`. The latter however requires C# 10.0, while the sourcegen
    projects are for whatever reason stuck at C# 9.0. Additionally
    `CachedAttributeData` already had the equality members autogenerated by
    Rider.

    Of particular note, inspecting the equality members reveals that
    `BackgroundDependencyLoaderAttributeData`'s equality members were
    probably not working good because they used reference comparisons on the
    `Parameters` array. This is changed to a full structural element-wise
    equality comparison instead.
---
